# NPC dialogue — prompt first, no masking cleanups (until gate)

When editing **`NPCDialogueManager.gd`** (especially **`_NPC_DIALOGUE_THREE_PASS`** paths):

1. **Do not add** Godot-side “repair” steps that make inconsistent LLM output look correct in logs or UI (e.g. unwrap JSON speech wrappers, normalize dialogue strings, typo-fix History, salvage ambiguous completions), **unless the user explicitly asks for that phase of work**.

2. **Gate before cleanups:** Treat automated cleanups as allowed only after the user has validated **~20–30 back-to-back turns** where the **raw** completions match the intended contract; occasional breakage after that is when targeted fixes belong.

3. **Raw logs = truth:** Rapid testing must reflect **what the model actually returned**. Parsing helpers that only **extract** strict structures (e.g. balanced `{…}` / `[…]` slices for JSON the prompt already requires) are fine; anything that **rewrites** model text to “what we wish it said” is not, until post-gate.

4. If unsure, **change prompts / instruct tuning / token limits** first; **do not** add masking layers by default.
